tasks.details:
1. Update tailwind.config.js with the new color palette:
```javascript
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        background: '#1abeff',
        foreground: '#0f33bb',
        primary: '#0f33bb',
        'primary-foreground': '#ffffff',
        secondary: '#ffffff',
        'secondary-foreground': '#0f33bb',
      },
      borderRadius: {
        xl: '12px',
      },
      fontFamily: {
        'cal': ['Cal Sans', 'sans-serif'],
        'satoshi': ['Satoshi', 'sans-serif'],
        'crimson': ['Crimson Pro', 'serif'],
      },
    },
  },
  // Ensure dark mode is configured properly
  darkMode: 'class',
}
```
2. Remove any existing red/green color definitions or create aliases that map to appropriate blue variants
3. Update any custom gradient definitions to match the blue/purple reference gradients
4. Ensure the configuration supports both light and dark modes

1. Download or import the required fonts:
   - Cal Sans: https://github.com/calcom/font
   - Satoshi: https://www.fontshare.com/fonts/satoshi
   - Crimson Pro: https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Crimson+Pro
2. Add the fonts to the project in a '/public/fonts/' directory
3. Create a fonts.css file with proper @font-face declarations:
```css
@font-face {
  font-family: 'Cal Sans';
  src: url('/fonts/CalSans-SemiBold.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 600;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
  font-family: 'Satoshi';
  src: url('/fonts/Satoshi-Variable.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 300 900;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
  font-family: 'Crimson Pro';
  src: url('/fonts/CrimsonPro-Variable.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 200 900;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}
```
4. Import the fonts.css file in the main layout or global CSS file
5. Update the default font-family in the global CSS to use Cal Sans as the primary font

1. Update the global CSS file with the new color variables:
```css
:root {
  --background: #1abeff;
  --foreground: #0f33bb;
  --primary: #0f33bb;
  --primary-foreground: #ffffff;
  --secondary: #ffffff;
  --secondary-foreground: #0f33bb;

  /* Add additional variables for gradients */
  --gradient-blue-purple: linear-gradient(135deg, #1abeff 0%, #7b61ff 100%);

  /* Add variables for rounded corners */
  --border-radius: 12px;
}

.dark {
  --background: #0a0a1e;
  --foreground: #1abeff;
  --primary: #1abeff;
  --primary-foreground: #ffffff;
  --secondary: #0f33bb;
  --secondary-foreground: #ffffff;
}
```
2. Ensure these variables are accessible throughout the application
3. Create a color utility module that provides functions for accessing these colors programmatically if needed
4. Document the color system for other developers

1. Locate all button component definitions (likely in a components/ui/button.tsx or similar)
2. Update the button styles to use the new color scheme:
```jsx
// Primary button (white background, dark blue text)
const Button = ({ children, variant = 'primary', ...props }) => {
  const variants = {
    primary: 'bg-secondary text-primary font-cal rounded-xl transition-all hover:bg-opacity-90',
    secondary: 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground font-cal rounded-xl transition-all hover:bg-opacity-90',
    outline: 'border border-primary text-primary bg-transparent font-cal rounded-xl transition-all hover:bg-primary hover:bg-opacity-10',
    // Add other variants as needed
  };

  return (
    <button className={variants[variant]} {...props}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```
3. Ensure all button hover and focus states use appropriate color variations
4. Add subtle animations for button interactions (hover, focus, active)
5. Update any icon colors within buttons to match the new scheme
6. Ensure consistent rounded corners (12px/rounded-xl) across all buttons

1. Update input field styles:
```css
.input {
  border: 1px solid var(--primary);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  color: var(--primary);
  background-color: var(--secondary);
}

.input:focus {
  outline: 2px solid var(--primary);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```
2. Update select dropdowns, checkboxes, radio buttons, and other form elements
3. Ensure form validation states use appropriate blue variants instead of red/green
4. For error states, use darker blue (#0a2080) instead of red
5. For success states, use lighter blue (#5cc7ff) instead of green
6. Update focus and hover states to use the appropriate blue variants
7. Ensure consistent rounded corners (12px) across all form elements
8. Apply Cal Sans font to form labels and Satoshi for input text
